A primary Si–Air battery employing nanostructured silicon as anode material with an alkaline solution based electrolyte was investigated by Zhong et al. [23]. Typical galvanostatic discharge of the cell exhibited that the cell can be used to draw current at 0.05 mA cm−2 over a period of 30 h at an operating potential of 1.2 V. In contrast, in a control experiment using an unmodified silicon wafer, the cell is completely discharged in less than 10 min at a potential of 1.1 V i.e. the potential quickly drops to zero. The electrode reactions are:8Anode: Si+4OH-⇋SiOH4+4e-Eo=1.69V\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
